==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*xroba-, *xrosa-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''hrōf'', Old Saxon [[rof|rōf]] (Dutch [[roef]] ‘cabin, coffin-lid’), Old Norse [[hróf]] ‘boat-shed’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /hro:f/

===Noun===
'''hrōf''' ''m''
# [[roof]]
# ''(Poetic)'' the [[sky]] or [[heavens]]

